Kofun B is a {{nihongo|''[[zenpokoenfun|zenpō-kōen-fun]]''|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|2=ja|3=前方後円墳|4=ko|5=전방후원분|6=zh|7=前方後圓墳|lt=Zenpokoenfun|comement=second one attempting to fix this error|lt=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|comment=doing this because I need to differentiate it in piped links too with my new interwiki tool as not the ambiguous phrase keyhole shaped kofun|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun}}, which is shaped like a keyhole, having one square end and one circular end, when viewed from above. It has a total length of 51 meters, with a posterior circle diameter of 28 meters, height of six meters, and an anterior section with a width of eight meters and a height of three meters. A combination-style [[:en:Sarcophagus|Sarcophagus]] was discovered in the center of the posterior circular portion, containing the remains of two men and a woman. [[:en:Grave goods|Grave goods]] found in Kofun B and C included six [[:en:Bronze mirror|Bronze mirror]]s, ''[[magatama]]'' beads, jasper stone pieces, and dear antler-shaped swords. The jasper pieces were found to be parts of a stone chime, possibly a ''[[:en:bianqing|bianqing]]'', which had been purposely crushed and its fragments scattered near the remains. Based on the shape of the tumulus, the structure of the sarcophagus, and the excavated items, it is estimated to be the oldest [[:en:Kinai region|Kinai-style]] tumulus in the region, built in the early Kofun period.<ref name="Shiseki"/>
The site is now a park noted for its large profusion of [[:en:Lycoris radiata|red spider lilies]] in fall. It is located approximately 20 minutes by car from [[:en:Bungo-Taketa Station|Bungo-Taketa Station]] on the [[:en:Kyushu Railway Company|Kyushu Railway Company]] [[:en:Hōhi Main Line|Hōhi Main Line]].<ref name="Shiseki"/>
